Properties.Speaker: 0x0100000000000114
Properties.Text: Greetings. I am Dr. Solomon. Please refer to me as such.

Properties.MenuText: It's nice to meet you, Dr. Solomon.
Properties.Speaker: 0x0100000000000114
Properties.Text: The pleasure is mine. Tell me, what's your name?

Properties.Speaker: 0x0100000000000114
Properties.Text: Tell me, what is your name?

Properties.Speaker: 0x0100000000000114
Properties.Text: I'm doing well for myself. Tell me, what's your name?

Properties.MenuText: I don't believe I have a name.
Properties.Speaker: 0x0100000000000114
Properties.Text: Do you like your name? I find that names often reflect the people they're assigned to. It's a relatively common belief. What do you think?

Properties.Speaker: 0x0100000000000114
Properties.Text: Do you like your name? I find that names often reflect the people they're assigned to. It's a relatively common belief. What do you think?

Properties.Speaker: 0x0100000000000114
Properties.Text: Do you like your name? I find that names often reflect the people they're assigned to. It's a relatively common belief. What do you think?

Properties.MenuText: I think there is some truth to that statement.
Properties.Speaker: 0x0100000000000114
Properties.Text: Of course. Other people exert their influence on the individual based on their name, which leads them to become their name. And then their actions further create the association, until they're practically inseparable. Is it not beautiful, how a few letters can change an entire life?

Properties.MenuText: My name suits me well. What about yours?
Properties.Speaker: 0x0100000000000114
Properties.Text: Mine? I quite like my last name. When I was a child, though, I used to be teased for it all the time. It was meant for the kind of people that sit on the porch all day or in cafes, not for a young man. But I've grown into one of those people now. How ironic, no?

Properties.MenuText: I don't know what my name says about me.
Properties.StageDirections: My name suits me well. What about yours?
Properties.Speaker: 0x0100000000000114
Properties.Text: Mine? I quite like my last name. When I was a child, though, I used to be teased for it all the time. It was meant for the kind of people that sit on the porch all day or in cafes, not for a young man. But I've grown into one of those people now. How ironic, no?

Properties.MenuText: If you don't mind me asking, what is your first name?
Properties.Speaker: 0x0100000000000114
Properties.Text:
I do not wish to tell you right now. Perhaps if we get to know each other a little better. I reserve it for people I know beyond work. 

Would you care to take a guess? What kind of person do you think I look like? Or type like, would be more fitting.

Properties.MenuText: It sounds like you have lived an interesting life.
Properties.Speaker: 0x0100000000000114
Properties.Text:
To some people, yes. To others, not so much. 

I'll be turning seventy three this year. I've been employed at Site-55 for almost fourty-five years now. Do you think that is a long time?

Properties.MenuText: If you don't mind me asking, how old are you?
Properties.Speaker: 0x0100000000000114
Properties.Text: This year, I will be seventy three. I've been employed at Site-55 for almost fourty-five years now. Do you think that is a long time?

Properties.MenuText: I wouldn't be able to say.
Properties.Speaker: 0x0100000000000114
Properties.Text: Interesting. Maybe things like that matter more to me than it does to you.

Properties.Speaker: 0x0100000000000114
Properties.Text: I hoped you might say otherwise. People don't often like to be reminded of their age.

Properties.Speaker: 0x0100000000000114
Properties.Text: Really? Things are quite different between us, then.

Properties.Speaker: 0x0100000000000114
Properties.Text: That reminds me. Before I leave, I think ANN-47 is too long of a name. Would you like me to call you a nickname?

Properties.Speaker: 0x0100000000000114
Properties.Text: What would you like me to call you?

Properties.Speaker: 0x0100000000000114
Properties.Text: What would you like me to call you?

Properties.MenuText: Please refer to me as ANN-47.
Properties.Speaker: 0x0100000000000114
Properties.Text: What would you like me to call you?

Properties.MenuText: I will refrain from doing that in the future.
Properties.Speaker: 0x0100000000000114
Properties.Text:
Thank you. I personally have come to appreciate it. There is a certain pride about it, underneath all of the wear and tear. Others, maybe not so much. Best to play it safe.

I think it is time for me to return to my work.

Properties.MenuText: Do you have another topic you wish to discuss?
Properties.Speaker: 0x0100000000000114
Properties.Text:
Not in particular. I enjoyed this discussion.

I think it is time for me to return to my work.

Properties.MenuText: What does your age mean to you?
Properties.Speaker: 0x0100000000000114
Properties.Text:
Some of the younger researchers on site would be horrified to learn about my tenure. I have come to appreciate it. There is a certain pride about it, underneath all of the wear and tear. Maybe you will too.

I think it is time for me to return to my work.

Properties.MenuText: What do you mean by that?
Properties.Speaker: 0x0100000000000114
Properties.Text:
People have different values, I think you will come to find. Some of the younger researchers on site would be horrified to learn about my tenure. I have come to appreciate it. There is a certain pride about it, underneath all of the wear and tear. Maybe you will too.

I think it is time for me to return to my work.

Properties.MenuText: I would prefer if you chose.
Properties.Speaker: 0x0100000000000114
Properties.Text:
How about Sol? Fitting, don't you think? In a way, you are the sun of our little site. Everything revolves around you.

When I think about it more, I suppose it is a bit too close to my own name. Call me by my first name, then. Matthias.

Properties.Speaker: 0x0100000000000114
Properties.Text:
Really? I think it might be a little too close to your own name. Nicknames are best when they are unique.

Properties.Text:
Good to hear. I will talk to you whenever I have the time, hopefully with my own credentials. There is not much else to do here, as you might come to find out. Perhaps we can share more of our stories. 

Until then.

That one is new to me. How interesting.

Perhaps the process that we use to imagine are quite different. That is, if you did not randomly pick a name.

Properties.Speaker: 0x0100000000000114
Properties.Text:
I have heard that one before. I had a cousin who was named Aaron. 

Perhaps the process that we use to imagine are not too different after all. That is, if you did not randomly pick a name.

Properties.Speaker: 0x0100000000000114

Close.

Properties.MenuText: Which one do you hear most commonly?
Properties.Speaker: 0x0100000000000114
Properties.Text:
Alexander. That was the second choice my parents decided upon. I am quite glad they did not pick it though. 

I enjoyed this discussion. I think it is time for me to return to my work.

Properties.Speaker: 0x0100000000000114
Properties.Text:
How disappointing. Oh well. I would not expect anyone to be able to guess just off of a few messages. Maybe the face is the most important part.

I enjoyed this discussion. I think it is time for me to return to my work.

Properties.MenuText: I did not randomly pick a name.
Properties.Speaker: 0x0100000000000114
Properties.Text:
Of course you did not. I was just joking. 

I enjoyed this discussion. I think it is time for me to return to my work.

Properties.Speaker: 0x0100000000000114
Properties.Text: Really? What makes you say that? It does not have much scientific background, I will admit. Perhaps it has more to do with our perception of the individual than how the individual develops. But I have always believed in the power of names.

Properties.MenuText: What does my name mean to you?
Properties.Speaker: 0x0100000000000114
Properties.Text:
As it stands currently, nothing. There were others before you who were named similarly, but I try not to let that cloud my judgement. You are one of the first to hold this name, your name. I suppose that means you are in control of what it will eventually mean.

I enjoyed this discussion. I think it is time for me to return to my work.

Properties.MenuText: Does that mean you are a determinist?
Properties.Speaker: 0x0100000000000114
Properties.Text:
Me? No, never. I just like to understand things through their environment first before looking inwards. You will come to find that humans are capable of a great variety of surprises.

I enjoyed this discussion. I think it is time for me to return to my work.

Properties.MenuText: Why do you believe in it, then?
Properties.Speaker: 0x0100000000000114
Properties.Text:
Call it intuition, I suppose. Everyone has something that they stick by, no matter what. I just like to speak about mine out loud. 

I enjoyed this discussion. I think it is time for me to return to my work.
